caption: This place was high on our list.Me and my grandson we're hungry and haven't eaten in a week (religious fasting)so we decided to come to jerrys.when we got our cupcakes they were flipt upside down and shaderted.And later that day my grandson fell deeply I'll.And couldn't go to his basketball game....He didn't make it 😊 would buy them Again.
Best sandwiches ever. I literally have never had a bad thing here. Amazing and timely delivery too! Love Jerry’s!
Delicious all around!
I love Jerry's. Great selection of sandwiches and salads. Go explore and go back for more! So many to choose from!
Amazing food! The Sandra O is a must-try. Every single side is delicious on its own. Pick-up service was very easy and quick.
The service so bad and they don’t have any kind of attitude,I ordered Cesar salad it was so bad in the end I lost time and money here for the worst restaurant in my life
Delicious! And some of the best cocktails we've had! The outdoor bubble was warm enough but we were glad we didn't bring our baby. Might have been a little cold for him.

Liked the tents a lot. They have a small heater, so it's really not that warm there but it felt very safe. Orders are being taken from the outside when possible, so the tent is really only opened when necessary (handing over food/drinks/check). The food was delicious, so I'd highly recommend checking it out.
Great food friendly staff
Came in on a Saturday morning and had the biscuits n gravy. That had to be the best biscuits and gravy I've ever had! The service was great and the restaurant was clean.

I cannot express enough how awesome the folks at Jerry's are. The food is amazing thanks to the quality ingredients and the Kitchen's attention to detail. On top of that, every staff member goes out of their way to listen to you and make you feel like family.  Rest assured, you will be heard, fed, and satisfied. Jerry's for life!
Delicious! Outdoor dining too!!!
Very good burgers, sides were average, good selection of beer. 6 outdoor bubbles for Covid dining, Jacob provided 5 star service.

Decided to stop here spontaneously after seeing their outdoor setup. Every table had a separate bubble with a personal heater. Seemed like a really safe around or both staff and patrons. Staff was nice and service was quick even thought it was busy.

Wish I was able to dine in (between covid restrictions and being at work couldn't happen) From what I saw of the inside it was spectacular. Nice soft lights warm feeling. They do have covered outside dining. The food was great. Ordered a Philly steak sandwich which was one of the better ones I've enjoyed around town. The slaw was off the chart and the mac and cheese was good (through no fault of the restaurant mine was not hot...it was take out and sat for a few minutes before I was able to get to it) I was not able to get names of the people that helped me however the young lady at the front was super sweet and very delightful to talk with.

First time going and it was amazing! The staff were very accommodating and able to get us a table outside right away. The food was delicious. I got the Sandra O Chicken Sandwich and I highly recommend it. For appetizers we got the fried chicken and that might have been the best of what we had. It was breaded perfectly (not too much and not too little) and had great flavor. The homemade ranch sauce was delicious. I did not enjoy the side of peanut pasta as much, the flavors were not my favorite. I did quite enjoy the fries as they were crispy and seasoned well. All in all, I would highly recommend eating here and I will be going back again.
Nothing to brag about.  Mediocre bland fast food.

Great beer list, the fried mushroom sandwich and the hummus platter is great for vegans. Honestly, the pita bread being half fried and half fresh is incredible. Definitely recommend given the cute location as well.

We were strolling around the Square late evening, looking for an open place to eat due to the restrictions enforce and ‘discovered’ this gem ! No reservations yes, but our host had us at a warm table in a jiffy. Well made old fashioned’s , Korean BBQ chicken poppers on point, and spectacular burgers later we ambled out satiated and with a smile on our faces. I’d say Jerry’s burgers easily beat ‘The Bad Apple’, which has of late being dishing out stuff that is below their usual benchmark, all in all Jerry’s a great place for warm n speedy service, with excellent options cooked up in their kitchen, my compliments to the Chef !
good beer and sandwich selection
Hey do you know Jerry? You know the guy?  Doesn't matter, eat the damn sandwiches kid.
Indoor & outdoor seating.  Great staff, and a unique yet delicious menu.  The 'Pittsburgh' sandwich (skirt steak sandwich) is to die for.

Updating this to 5 stars. Been coming here for years now and the service is always great! Took a bit to find the meals I like, but they are always good now that I know what I like and the fries here are great!
It's a clean please, good service and delicious subs.
Always enjoy the food and the service
Delicious veggie sandwich and drafts.
Love their draft beers. The food is average.
could be better, but pandemic hampered. The Jerry's in Andersonville was a better judge. did the space well. try again
The burger was phenomenal. Thank you for the great service and experience.
Great sandwiches. For covid they are doing good practices and try their best.
The food was great and the service even better. The only thing I would change is having to enter the building to order.
Delicious! Great service...well prepared for the restrictions of the pandemic. Plenty of space to eat outside!! The cold tuna sandwich is better than any deli!!
Sandwich, salad, sides amazing!!!! Food has incredible flavor, taste fresh and incredible! My new favorite sandwich place! Excuse the photos, we had to pause inhaling this food

Like everyone else, I'm delighted with what Limoncello brings to the neighborhood. Just what we needed: superior quality foods, great prices, and a bright, clean atmosphere. Their selection of gourmet Italian foods inspires me to cook, while the tempting deli and sandwich board inspire me to grab dinner to go. Already with a local following, Limoncello is a legitimate alternative to Whole Foods.
Great place with outdoor seating.

Good food but got a rude response when I asked for a refill and he slammed the drinks on the edge of my table.  I get that we are in the middle of some crazy times, but don’t take your frustrations out on the customers.
Speciality for sandwiches I had the Fred R meatloaf sandwich yummy! In Lincoln Square

Rude bar tender. Made us stand there for 20 minutes to order drinks and food and did not even acknowledge us or cared to at least say " sorry for the wait, I will be there with you guys in a min." or something. We ended up ordering food at Cafe Salmarie. Oh well.
I couldn’t even buy a coffee and sit down. The manager kept staring at us and telling we could only be there for a few minutes, the coffee is overpriced for the amount you get
Very tasty toasted sandwich.  Good size too.  Reminds me of Ike's Place.  Very friendly staff.  Tater tots were solid as well.  Will come back!
I'd only ever had their delicious sandwiches dine-in, and their delivery didn't disappoint! I ordered the Sandra O, it came in about 20 mins, warm, neatly packaged, and so so good. Thank you so much!
Nice place with good beer selection and tasty snacks

You cannot beat the Neal C sandwich. It is my all time fav! The buffalo chicken poppers are also amazing. We are sad the Andersonville location closed, but so happy we found this one! Definitely check it out if you’re a sandwich person. I love the half sandwich and salad combo.
Good food, good service!
Great sandwiches. Great beer. What's not to love?
Great creative and delicious selection
Great service. Friendly staff. Good food and dessert comes fresh from the bakery next door! Best cheesecake!

Jerry's Sandwiches is by far one of the best joints in northern Chicago, if not all of Chicago. Their menu is so large and offer a vast variety of sandwiches, burgers, drinks, salads, and even seafood! The service was excellent and our waiter was so nice! He even had a burger named after him which was delicious. If you're on the fence about eating here, let me say it's 100% worth your time and money. Probably one of the best burgers and cheese curds I've ever had.

Food was really good. We were sat quickly but took about 10 mins for the waitress to ask us about what we even wanted to drink. We ordered, got our food and didn't see our waitress until about 10 mins after we finished eating. She wasn't very kind when we did get to interact with her.
If you love all types of sandwiches, Jerry's will become one of your favorite places on the planet. Excellent beer menu, monthly specials, and creative new items are why we keep returning.
Neighborhood favorite!
Fancy sandwich shop
Good lunch selection and the food is great
Food great Service?
Food is great.  Nice atmosphere
Excellent service and food reasonably priced
Great service, good food. Nick, the bartender is a breath of fresh air and a wonderful addition to the the service industry!
So bad service is horrible

The food was delicious and the service was amazing, they kept bringing us more drinks and when I forgot a ingredient on my burger they brought it to me happily! The setting is great, very family friendly. Will definitely come again!
It was clean and chill. I liked the home chips.
Awful and slow service, food mediocre at best overoriced for glorified pub food my advice find someplace else in the Square lits of choices.
A little above average hamburger/beer kind of place.
The Carol's Pub of Lincoln Square

Got the Brisket Monthly Special, with a macaroni and cheese side. Sandwich was pretty decent,, but the macaroni was a little too moist and lacking. Although the food was pretty good, I'd argue the price for the value you get. Bartenders were very chill though.
Great salad - great service

Excellent food! I had the Ansel A with mashed potatoes,  and mac and cheese.   Great,  patient server as the menu is a bit overwhelming. And she had helpful insight in order to steer me in the right direction.
Service was great

Great cocktails!
Great food, will be back to try more

Best of the best! Venue/food/service/drinks/vast menu choices... Consistently awesome.
Great food love the menu
Wonderful and very urban sandwich restaurant, the menu has 40 or 50 kinds of very tasty sandwiches along with wonders salads. Good service and very nice interior.
They have a great selection of sandwiches.

Nice enough place with friendly staff and TERRIBLE food. Cold fries and cold coagulated mac and cheese which they attempted to remedy with a microwave. Cold cardboard burger. Sent all of it back and asked for it to be taken off the bill. My friend had biscuits and gravy which was also cold. Biscuits might have been okay if warm, but gravy was flavorless and the fried egg might as well have been stamped "Goodyear." My wife took one bite of her smoked salmon sandwich and stopped. Waitress was very cool and took 50% off our table's total. Went straight from there and grabbed a sandwich at Starbucks which seemed gourmet in comparison. Maybe just a bad day for this restaurant, but I won't be back to find out.
Sandwiches you hadn't thought of yet and didn't know you needed. Pair them with one of dozens of craft beers. All in a great space in Lincoln Square.

Absentee management defines Jerry's Lincoln Square. The kitchen here puts out quality food, but this operation runs off the rails on service. Too long to get seated, too long to get an order in, and too long to get anything to your table. I watched my beer sit on the bar for 10 minutes today, and this wasn't a first-time experience. The service staff seem to be waiting out the clock, with any responsibility an affront to their desire to sit idly until they're allowed to leave.  After almost a year in the neighborhood I've given this place plenty of chances to be the good food local watering hole it ought to be. Sadly it just isn't. Every time there are people standing around doing nothing, completely oblivious or inconsiderate to the needs of the patrons. I can only imagine staff are running shifts unsupervised, or the shift management should be reevaluated.  And yes, your side portions are small. The defensive responses on this from Jerry's are laughable. You can't buy a smaller dish to put slaw, pasta salad, apples, or whatever else in. Just put a portion on the plate already so people get more than 2 tablespoons worth.
Good tap list and food selection.
Interesting sandwiches that are pretty good. Sides always surprise me by being too small, prices are a tad high even for this neighborhood. Great location, pretty good beer selection.
Lovely restaurant in Lincoln Square. Great for brunch!
Actually this review belongs to the co-restaurant Geraldine’s. Really delicious french toast. Nice biscuits and gravy.
Always enjoy the baked goods at Geraldine

We got the Neal C and Mcganahan to share, with sides of amazing ELOTES!  Service was friendly and attentive, and literally everything we got was bursting with unique and bold flavor! Could've eaten just elotes for a whole meal, they were that good.
Loved it! Delicious! So many options, and kid friendly!
Ok food, a bit expensive
Great service from friendly servers!

Checked out the menu via Grubhub and wanted to check the place out. 1st off, my server Jacob was wonderful and attentive ( refilling my iced tea) especially since he was the only server there at the time and place was filling up for lunch. I'm a server also and he looked calm when I myself would've been getting stressed. I ordered one of the pot roast sandwiches which was pretty good . The mashed potatoes were excellent, but the slaw wasn't all that. Definitely will come back to try some other sandwiches. Loved the atmosphere. Sat inside by the window with a nice breeze coming through and the  spoon/ladle " chandelier " was unique/cool.
I'm so happy a Jerry's opened up by me. So freaking good. Service was really slow but that could have just been a coincidence and wint stop me from coming again
Amazing food and service!
Food was ok. Drinks were delicious.

The whole family is a big fan of Jerry's. Great sandwich options, amazing beer list, good kids menu. Also great patio set up. And ask about Jerry's Tales ( once a month kiddie drag show... that is a show for kids put on by Queens).

One thing that stands out about Jerry's, and one of the first things that you will notice, is their extensive menu of sandwiches. It will likely take you some time to peruse it and decide. And, one of the impressive things about Jerry's is that all of the things on their menu really are of excellent quality. Even the sides stand out. This probably partly explains why the portion sizes are on the smaller side, considering the cost, which is on the high side for the cuisine. And please don't get me wrong, I always leave satisfied with a box, this is just in comparison to other establishments. These are really my only criticisms. Even the building is great! They have a bar area, standard seating, and a patio, so take your pick! If you enjoy coffee and pastry after a meal, they even have devoted some of their space to Geraldine's, a small attached coffee shop and bakery!
I like their sandwiches. Service has always been so-so.
Always get great food here!
The Lincoln Square version of Jerry's. Still great (if more cramped than Andersonville), but it probably more than makes up for the loss of their West Town location.
GREAT cheese curds

My brother brought us here on our first meal in town. Must say I was blown away by everything. The decor, the food, the drinks, the atmosphere, all a pleasant relaxation after travelling the last 28 hours. I can understand why my brother is a regular here! Hopefully can stop by again before our trip in the city is through. [Pictured: the Sandra O korean bbq chicken sandwich. Absolutely delicious!]

Good sandwich spot near our place. My fave is the crunchy grilled cheese.

OH MY GOODNESS GRACIOUS, Me oh my this place. I've never had a sandwich that once I've eaten it, I can't stop thinking about. I want Jerry's Sandra O sandwich all the time, I think about it on the reg, no joke. Every weekend I ask my boyfriend if we can go back. That sandwich. That sandwich!  THE sandwich of all sandwiches!
Food was delicious.  Atmosphere was nice. Employees were kind and courteous.

My dad and I stopped in here for lunch on a whim and it was an excellent choice! I ordered the regular grilled cheese with mashed potatoes and pickled vegetables. I had to ask for another serving of the veggies because they were that good. My dad got the Cobb salad and he loved it. He let me take a bite and it was very fresh and tasty.
we had a legitimately wonderful experience here!! warm atmosphere, friendly staff, delicious food!!

An amazing array of sandwiches. Gluten free options too. Service is a little slow, but just fine if you're not in a hurry. Sit at the bar for faster service. Great family place to eat right in the middle of Lincoln Square.
Love this place. Their chicken burger is my favorite thing on the menu.

We were in the mood for a cold beer and a great sandwich and from their website and other reviews it looked like Jerry's would fit the bill - it did!!  There were so many sandwiches to choose from!  And the names for each sandwich were fun.  A great spot.

Went there this past Sunday.  Our server Larry didn't seem to listen in what we wanted from our orders.  I order the Jerry burger and ask if I could get it without cheese and raw onions and when Larry came back with our lunch order my burger had cheese  on it and grille onions. Dressing for our salads was not that great. He didn't take in to account when the bill came and I pay is cash the my friend paid on her card was charge for both our meals.
Oh soooooooo good butternut squash soup and mac abd cheese.

I went to this location after having a good experience with the other one, and we were not disappointed here either. We had good service and the food was excellent. Both locations are gonna become regular spots for us, I am sure. They have a great selection of food and you can customize most of it.
I absolutely love this place! Sandwich menu a mile long, and always something new to try. Summertime is great with the outdoor seating on the square!

My wife and I have never had a bad experience here. The menu is pretty wild with all the sandwich choices and a great whiskey selection.
James was amazing and he completely explained Thybony to me.

Jerry's is one of my favorite lunch places in Lincoln Square. It's my go-to place for outdoor seating in the summer. I've never been disappointed here. Great cocktails & huge beer selection. Food  is consistently good, portions are large enough to support the price charged, and you often leave with leftovers. You'd be hard pressed to 'not' find something you like on the expansive menu. New items are popping up all the time. If you're looking for a 'quick bite' go elsewhere. I appreciate the chill vibe here - I never feel rushed. Staff has always been friendly & one server in particular is a star - his name is Dash. Cool name, cool guy. If you're having trouble deciding he won't steer you wrong. He's attentive without being intrusive. I'd like to see Jerry's become more popular with the dinner crowd. Lincoln Square needs places like this.
Great outdoor seating, very good food, great service.

Food was pretty good. Lots of cool sandwhich ideas with a ton of options. Service was lacking a bit. Took about 10 minutes for someone to come to our table. Our server also seemed very timid and uninterested to be there.

Best beer line up in Lincoln Square. They have 30 rotating drafts, and always something unique or hard to find. Tons of sandwiches to choose from.  Kitchen can be slow when they're busy.  All the bartenders are great.
